<TITLE> New BERC chief named </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, November 5 (bdnews24.com)Retired secretary Golam Rahman has been appointed chairman of the Bangladesh Energy Regulatory Commission, the Press Information Department said in a statement Monday. Rahman has been made chief of the BERC for a three-year term on contract to be effective on the date he assumes office. Rahman's appointment is as per the BERC Ordinance, 2003, the handout said. Rahman had also carried out responsibilities as secretary to the Prime Minister's Office and the shipping and commerce ministries. bdnews24.c
